Add tests for errors struct returned by $fails->build_struct()

rebuild-tests.pl now allows the following in spec/schemata files:

  "type" : {
    "input" : {
      "errors" : errors,
      "errors_struct" : errors_struct
    }
  }

in addition to the original:

  "type" : {
    "input" : errors
  }

The structure of spec/spec.json is the same, with the addition of
errors_struct where specified.

Improve errors for invalid values in //str, //num, and //int

//num and //int should output the short type name, instead of the full uri.
//str should not call type_name(), which no longer exists.
Avoid uninitialized value warning when the value is undefined.

Adding build_struct() to Data::Rx::Failures - work in progress

Creates a structure mirroring the original data structure, but containing
just the errors that occurred.

For example:

  data: { bar: 1, baz: "a", quux: 1 }

  schema: { type: "//rec",
            required: { foo: "//int", bar: "//int", baz: "//int" }
          }

  errors: { foo: "missing", baz: "type", quux: "unexpected" }

Does not yet handle cases where a value should be both an error and a hash
or array ref, as can happen with //all.

